6. Write C programs to simulate the following memory management techniques a) Paging b) 
Segmentation


ðŸ§  Memory Management Techniques
a) Paging
ðŸ“Œ Concept

Logical address = Page Number + Offset

Physical address = Frame Number + Offset

Page table maps page â†’ frame

âœ… C Program: Paging Simulation
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int page_table[10];
    int n, page_size;
    int page_no, offset, frame_no, phys_addr;

    printf("Enter number of pages: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Enter page size: ");
    scanf("%d", &page_size);

    printf("Enter page table (page -> frame):\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d", &page_table[i]);

    printf("Enter page number and offset: ");
    scanf("%d %d", &page_no, &offset);

    if (page_no >= n || offset >= page_size) {
        printf("Invalid logical address\n");
        return 0;
    }

    frame_no = page_table[page_no];
    phys_addr = frame_no * page_size + offset;

    printf("Physical Address = %d\n", phys_addr);

    return 0;
}

b) Segmentation
ðŸ“Œ Concept

Logical address = Segment Number + Offset

Each segment has base address and limit

Physical address = Base + Offset

âœ… C Program: Segmentation Simulation
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int n;
    int base[10], limit[10];
    int seg_no, offset, phys_addr;

    printf("Enter number of segments: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Enter base and limit for each segment:\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        scanf("%d %d", &base[i], &limit[i]);

    printf("Enter segment number and offset: ");
    scanf("%d %d", &seg_no, &offset);

    if (seg_no >= n || offset >= limit[seg_no]) {
        printf("Invalid logical address\n");
        return 0;
    }

    phys_addr = base[seg_no] + offset;

    printf("Physical Address = %d\n", phys_addr);

    return 0;
}

ðŸ”¹ Sample Output (Paging)
Enter number of pages: 3
Enter page size: 100
Enter page table:
5 9 1
Enter page number and offset: 1 20
Physical Address = 920

ðŸ”¹ Sample Output (Segmentation)
Enter number of segments: 2
Enter base and limit:
1000 400
2000 300
Enter segment number and offset: 0 200
Physical Address = 1200

ðŸ§  Viva Comparison
Feature	Paging	Segmentation
Unit	Page	Segment
Size	Fixed	Variable
Address	Page + Offset	Segment + Offset
Fragmentation	Internal	External
